Gauteng premier David Makhura says the Johannesburg inner city has become a hotspot over the past week. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Premier David Makhura says the Johannesburg inner city has become a COVID-19 hotspot. Makhura was speaking at a briefing where he delivered updates on the number of COVID-19 infections in the province. READ:Â SA sees record jump in coronavirus cases "In terms of the number of active cases, there is an area from Rosebank to the CBD of Johannesburg and to Mayfair, that would be an area of great concern to us," said Makhura. Last month, Makhura warned that the province could revert to higher levels of the lockdown should the infection rate spike. South Africa has a total of 40,792 COVID-19 infections and 848 fatalities. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8 am to 4 pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.